now, as for the gold system, you use status variables.  ill code a simple buying system, and you can use it and expand it if you wish....

[code:2p31rx6k]
define game &lt;gold&gt;
	asl-version &lt;311&gt;
	start &lt;shop&gt;
   game info &lt;wotever&gt;

' this is where the status variable is implimented

	define variable &lt;gold&gt;
		type numeric
		value &lt;200&gt;
		display &lt;Gold&#58; !&gt;
	end define
end define

define synonyms
end define

define room &lt;shop&gt;
	command &lt;buy sword&gt; &#123;
		if &#40; %gold% &lt;= 149 &#41; then msg &lt;|bYou do not have enough gold|xb&gt;
		if &#40; %gold% &gt;= 150 &#41; then &#123;
			msg &lt;|bYou perchased a Sword|xb|n&gt;
			give &lt;sword&gt;
			set &lt;gold; %gold% - 150&gt;
		&#125;
	&#125;
end define

define room &lt;shop items&gt;

	define object &lt;sword&gt;
	end define

end define
[/code:2p31rx6k]

You can change the item, command, and money, but this script will decrease the gold amount depending on how much you set it too, and if the amount of gold you have is less than the gold needed to buy the item, it says [b:2p31rx6k]You do not have enough gold[/b:2p31rx6k]

